      • putValuesInHash

        private void putValuesInHash(SimpleHashtable hash,
                             java.lang.String valueName,
                             int number)
        Method which puts given number of values in the hash table. Values stored will be strings which consist of valueName to which an index is appended. Keys are string with value "key" to which an index is appended.
        Parameters:
        hash - hash table in which values will be put.
        valueName - value which will be put in the table. Values are strings which have incremental index added to the end of this string.
        number - number of values to be stored in the hash table.
